				\begin{document}$$y={A}_{1}{e}^{-t/{\tau }_{1}}+{A}_{2}{e}^{-t/{\tau }_{2}}$$\end{document}, with τ1 ~ 0.7 µs and τ2 ~ 10 µs. As shown in the inset of Fig. 2a, we observed the same τ1 and τ2 when using 517-nm and 638-nm lasers (Supplementary Fig. 5), suggesting that the time constants are intrinsic to the sample and independent on the laser wavelength. In contrast, the TRPL data on Sample A (Fig. 2b) exhibit two different times τf ~ 150 ns and τs ~ 0.7 µs, which will be discussed in the next section. By parking the tip at various locations of the film and measuring the decay curves, we also show that the tr-iMIM response is spatially uniform on the sample surface within statistical errors (Supplementary Figs. 6 and 7).Fig. 2Time-resolved iMIM and carrier lifetime.
